Australia Newcastle Thermal Coal Rises 1.3% to $122.45 a Ton

-- B y   R a k t e e m   K a t a k e y
-- 
2011-07-08T12:25:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-08/australia-newcastle-thermal-coal-rises-1-3-to-122-45-a-ton.html
Power-station coal  prices  at
 Australia ’s Newcastle port, an Asian benchmark, increased 1.3
percent in the week ended today.  Coal prices at the New South Wales port rose to $122.45 a
metric ton from $120.90 the previous week, according to the
 globalCOAL NEWC Index .  Xstrata Plc (XTA) , the world’s largest exporter of power-station
coal,  BHP Billiton Ltd. (BHP)  and Rio Tinto Group are among mining
companies that ship coal through Newcastle.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rakteem Katakey in  New Delhi  at 
 rkatakey@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Amit Prakash at 
 aprakash1@bloomberg.net  